<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Originally I know there were no plans for long range communication.  I really hope they stick to that, because being able to simply send tells or shouts to people whom are nowhere near you would all but destroy the RvR pvp aspect of the game.  If people can simply send tells to the rest of their realm, it would be impossible for a small group to adventure outside their realm.  The first person they encounter would give warning, and half the enemy realm would be on them in no time.  I prefer rather that a small group can sneak in, if they encounter a small group from the other realm, they could take them out without warning being spread.<P>The opposing realm could still give warning, but they would have to travel near where other players are to give that warning.  Allowing the adventuring party time to gather reinforcements or to relocate to another spot.<P>Allowing for tells or realm wide shouts would make it impossible for anyone to explore another realm without a full 40-50 person raiding party.<P>--------------------<P>"When in panic, when in doubt.  Run in circles, sceam and shout."<P>Explorer 66% | Killer 53% | Achiever 46% | Socializer 33%<P>NF idealist(figures)
</FONT>
